# Machine Options

## Source Functions — `src/lib/chain.ts`
| Function | Returns |
|----------|---------|
| `getAllMachineOptions()` | Full catalog (extractors + all recipes), cached |
| `getMachineOptionsForInput(itemKey)` | Recipes that consume `itemKey` + power-generator pseudo-options for supported fuels |
| `getMachineOptionsForProduct(itemKey)` | All recipes (+ extractors) that produce `itemKey` |
| `getExtractorMachineOptionsFull()` | All miner/pump options (pseudo `recipeKey = _raw_<resource>_<building>`) |
| `sortOptionsNonAltFirst(opts)` | Sorts standard recipes before alternates |

## Alternate Recipes
`recipeName.startsWith("Alternate")` → alternate.  
`AddMachineModal` has a `showAlternates` checkbox (default **off**) that filters them out.

## `childOptions` in `TreeLevelSlices.tsx`
Determines what is "recommended" when adding a machine next to an existing node:

| Context | Recommended options |
|---------|-------------------|
| No `outputItemKey` on parent | `getAllMachineOptions()` (no filter) |
| `sliceIdx === 0` and `parent.node.isRaw` | Extractors for **same resource** + `getMachineOptionsForInput(parent.outputItemKey)` |
| `sliceIdx > 0` | `getMachineOptionsForInput` for every `outputItemKey` across all previous slices |
| Default | `getMachineOptionsForInput(parent.outputItemKey)` |

`isFiltered = true` whenever `options` is a subset; `allOptions = getAllMachineOptions()` is then passed to the modal so the "Other" section appears.

## `AddMachineModal` Props
```ts
options: MachineOption[]      // recommended subset (or full list if unfiltered)
allOptions?: MachineOption[]  // full catalog — triggers Recommended/Other split when provided
```
When `allOptions` is omitted, all options are shown in a single flat list.

## Power Generator Extension — `src/lib/powerGenerators.ts`
- Adds pseudo machine options (e.g. `_power_fuel-generator_fuel`) without replacing base recipe DB.
- `getRecipeInputsPerMinute` checks these pseudo keys first so flow simulation can consume fuel/water inputs correctly.
- Power pseudo-options output synthetic item key `power` for display and sink modeling.
